This folder contains simple examples of sitar descriptions.
Each example illustrates a construct in the language.


For each description, a user has to first translate
the sitar description into C++ code, and then compile 
the code along with sitar core classes to obtain 
a simulation executable.

For running 0_HelloWorld.sitar example:

	$ sitar translate 0_HelloWorld.sitar
	$ sitar compile
	$ ./sitar_sim

type $ sitar translate -h for detailed information on translation options
and  $ sitar compile   -h for detailed information on compilation options.

